%N A395394 Decimal expansion of the volume of the solid of revolution formed by rotating a unit half-width lemniscate of Bernoulli about the vertical axis.
%C A395394 The lemniscate of Bernoulli can be described by (x^2 + y^2)^2 = a^2*(x^2 - y^2) in Cartesian coordinates, or r^2 = a^2*cos(2*phi) in polar coordinates, where a is the half-width. Here we take a = 1.
%D A395394 Babu Ram, Engineering Mathematics, Pearson, 2009. See example 8.15.
%H A395394 Mandeep Beniwal, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MBXioI6FQhM">Volume of solid of revolution of lemniscate</a>, Smart study helper, YouTube video, 2021.
